I. Basic style element overview

    buttons -> primarily for forms

    progress bars -> for interface for progress.

    list groups  -> useful for mobile projects. 

II. Create Buttons 
    
    Button Options:
        * btn: basic class
        * btn-SIZ
            SIZ: sm | lg
        * Can be used on: <a> | <button> | <input>

    Button Colors:
        * btn-COLOR
            primary | secondary | success | danger
            warning | info | light | dark

        * btn-outline-COLOR 
            primary | secondary | success | danger
            warning | info | dark 

    Other options:
        * btn-block: full width
        * active 
        * disabled

    (!) Can add margin classes



III. Button groups 
    Button Group Classes:
        * btn-group 
        * btn-group-vertical
        * btn-toolbar

IV. Use badges 

    Badge Classes:
        * badge 
        * badge-pill
        * badge-COLOR

    Badges are contextual. They will change size to fit container.

V. Progress bar styles 

    Progress Classes:
        * progress: containers 
        * progress-bar: item
        * Style width, height
        * Label text

    Progress Styles:
        * Use bg-COLOR
            success | info | warning | danger 
        * progress-bar-striped
        * progress-bar-animated
        * Multiple bars

    Accessibility Properties:
        * role="progressbar"
        * aria-valuenow: current value of bar
        * aria-valuemin: hold minumum value of element
        * aria-valuemax: hold maximum value of element

        Progress bar does not have an html element, so specifying role is important for screen readers.
        Div are harder for screen readers to understand.

VI. List groups 

    List Group Classes:
        * list-group: containers
        * list-group-item: items
        * li | button | a

    List Group Styles:
        * active | disabled 
        * list-group-item-action: style 
        * Use list-group-item-COLOR
            COLOR: primary | secondary | success | danger | warning | info | light | dark

        By default, list are stacked vertically.
        * list-group-horizontal(-BP)
         BP: sm >576px | md >768 | lg >992px | xl >1200px

    Adding Badges (common):
        * badge: classes
        * justify-content-between


VII. Breadcrumbs 

    Indicates where you are in navigation structure of site or for secondary navigation.

    Breadcrumb Links:
        * breadcrumb: containers
        * breadcrumb-item: items 
        * active: style
        * li | nav>a

VIII. Shadows 

    Shadows:
        * shadow-none
        * shadow-sm
        * shadow 
        * shadow-lg

Quiz:

1. Breadcrumbs are used to display channels within a website.
2. Option most handy for mobile devices.
    A: btn-block
